<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="cb040bf7-be28-5704-91a7-22d35a159ba8" activityNameId="6299360d-1116-4ab5-be76-abfa11a12e94" parentActivityId="30de0de4-71cb-4a45-a64f-abfa11b94499" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of waste polyethylene, unsanitary landfill, dry infiltration class (100mm)</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to air via landfill gas, and to water via leachate.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'waste polyethylene' in an unsanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: for PE, which goes to disposal as part of managed communal waste mixture. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% PE.   </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 41.63 MJ/kg; net heating value 39.01 MJ/kg; H2O 4000; O na; H 140500; C 842870; S 488.02; N 692.75; P na; B na; Cl 1505.3; Br 9.8766; F 14.815; I na; Ag na; As 1.7511; Ba 246.91; Cd 34.962; Co 1.7284; Cr 12.84; Cu 42.605; Hg 0.049383; Mn 30.947; Mo na; Ni 0.98766; Pb 23.272; Sb 10.37; Se 1.9354; Sn 3.9282; V 2271.6; Zn 352.24; Be 0.46081; Sc na; Sr 81.563; Ti 921.61; Tl 0.36864; W na; Si na; Fe 1580.3; Ca 2666.7; Al 184.32; K na; Mg 98.766; Na 1350.6.   </text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Share of carbon in initial waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 1%. 0.0007254 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents a landfill of 'infiltration class 2 dry'. Landfill site with mean annual temperature (MAT) of 8 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 550 mm/year, and net infiltration of 100 mm/year. Temperature at site can result in permafrost conditions, which slows down water flow by a factor of (alpha t) 0.999. Total climate adjustments with alpha pt of 0.999. The leachate percolating through the landfill has an average residence time of 37.5 years.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">Reference for climatic parameters: Doka, G., 2018, Inventory parameters for regionalised waste disposal mixes</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for an unsanitary, sub-controlled landfill for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average landfill height is 15 meters. Operation phase duration is 25 years. The total raw landfill gas mass produced in the landfill from this waste is 0.00887 kg. The total CH4 mass in the raw landfill gas is 0.006213 kg. Percentage of landfill gas directly emitted is 100w%. Leachate of the landfill is not treated, but emitted untreated. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 16577 years after waste deposition. </text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2006-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
